unit.name: 2 SS Panzer Division "Das Reich" HQ
unit.History: In 1940 the SS Division Verfügungstruppe was formed from several formerly independent regiments, and campaigned in the West. Early in 1941 the division was renamed "Das Reich". It took part in the campaign in Yugoslavia and fought in Russia. In September 1942 the division was transferred to France, and re-equipped as a panzergrenadier division. In March 1943 it was back in Russia to take part in the Charkow counteroffensive. In October 1943 it was redesignated as a panzer division. In the spring of 1944 it was sent to France yet again. The division was committed in Normandy, and was later rebuilt to about 80% strength. On December 16, 1944 it was part of the II SS Panzerkorps, which was held in reserve to exploit the expected breakthrough.

commander.Name: Heinz Lammerding
commander.PersBio: Lammerding served in the engineer battalion of the Verfügungsdivision before taking command of an infantry regiment. During 1942-1943 he was engaged in anti-partisan operations in the Soviet Union. He was given the command of "Das Reich" in January 1944, apparently more because of his close relation with Heinrich Himmler than because of his qualities as a military commander. Wounded in Normandy, he resumed command of the division in time for Operation Wacht am Rhein.
